race.comment: MRS PENNY CRACKER (10) backed up her narrow defeat with a barnstorming win last month, putting them away with authority. First look at the 2000m but expect her to be blending into race beautifully at the turn and be storming home. GARCON RENARD (6) kicked off the prep with an eye-catching win and has since been threatening to repeat the dose. He also has his first look at this trip but is drawn perfectly for Toeroek. Big chance. ANGIEMARIE (16) has good early toe, and is another sighting 2000m for the first time. Gets in light and could prove tough to run down. TALENT SCOUT (15) disappointed last time but was good fresh over the mile at Seymour. Should get a beautiful run in transit under Milnes and be right there when they quicken. Don't underestimate.
